A docstring
(short for documentation string) is a special string in Python used to describe what a module, function, class, or method does. It helps others (and you!) understand the code and is accessible at runtime.

‚úÖ What makes a string a docstring?

It is written as the first statement inside a module, function, class, or method.

It uses triple quotes: """ ... """ (or ''' ... ''').

Python stores it in the __doc__ attribute.